Schaeuble Says Stabilizing the Euro Is Essential, Leipziger Says

-- B y   C h r i s   R e i t e r
-- 
2011-09-04T11:44:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-04/schaeuble-says-stabilizing-the-euro-is-essential-leipziger-says.html
German Finance Minister  Wolfgang Schaeuble  said stabilizing the euro is worth “every effort”
because it secures growth, prosperity and jobs, the Leipziger
Volkszeitung  reported , citing on an interview.  “The euro is the engine of European integration,”
Schaeuble told the newspaper. “Without project  Europe , no
single state, including  Germany , would have good chances for
development in the ever more globalizing world.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Reiter in Berlin at 
